         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>The collection of the Miracles of Mary is one of the most popular works of Gǝʿǝz literature.
               It circulates as collections of varying constitution, of which the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5673AkkonuColl">Miracles of
                                                  Mary: ʾAkko-nu bəʾsi collection</t:ref> is the most standardised one.
                In the unpublished list compiled by William
               Macomber, <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/9PSXFIQK"><seg type="document"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:MacomberMiracles"/><title level="m">Miracles of Mary</title><author><forename>William</forename><surname>Macomber</surname></author><date>n.d.</date><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:MacomberMiracles</note></note><note type="tag">bm:MacomberMiracles</note></t:bibl>, 
               642 individual miracles are listed.</t:p>
            <t:p>This record refers to any collection of the Miracles of Mary declared as such and
               containing in addition to the miracles also introductory texts such as the <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1968Mashaf">Maṣḥafa śǝrʿāt
                                                  za-waṣʾa ʾǝm-manbara Mārqos ḥawāryā ʾǝm-makāna
                                                  maʿāllǝqā</t:ref>. For groups of miracles of Mary without introductory texts,
               see <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3585Taamme">Taʾammǝra
                                                  Māryām</t:ref>, for the so-called <t:foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾAkko-nu bǝʾsi</t:foreign> collection of 33 miracles, see
               <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5673AkkonuColl">Miracles of
                                                  Mary: ʾAkko-nu bəʾsi collection</t:ref>.</t:p>
         </t:abstract>
